&lt;h3 id=&quot;Root-Route---Conditional-Rendering&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Root-Route---Conditional-Rendering&quot; aria-label=&quot;Root Route   Conditional Rendering permalink&quot; class=&quot;gatsby-remark-autolink before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Root Route - Conditional Rendering&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now, let&apos;s revisit the conditional rendering portion of the root route (/). If the end user of the application is &quot;signed in&quot; and authenticated (passport) to visit the site, they will be presented with the &lt;em&gt;GetProfile&lt;/em&gt; component which will allow the user to create a site profile that will be associated with the user&apos;s account. Otherwise, if the user is not authenticated, they will guided through the GetAuthenticated workflow. Following the completion of the GetAuthenticated workflow and is signed in, the user will then be presented with the &lt;em&gt;GetProfile&lt;/em&gt; component. Pretty cool!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3 id=&quot;One-More-Route---Reg-Route&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#One-More-Route---Reg-Route&quot; aria-label=&quot;One More Route   Reg Route permalink&quot; class=&quot;gatsby-remark-autolink before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;One More Route - Reg Route&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So... I have one more route too. It is pictured below and is also a dynamic route that accepts a single param, &lt;em&gt;profileType&lt;/em&gt;. This route is called upon from the &lt;em&gt;GetProfile&lt;/em&gt; component and aligns with the profile type that you have selected to create, once you are authenticated to use the site.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For example, if you select the AthleteProfile from the &lt;em&gt;GetProfile&lt;/em&gt; component, you will be presented with the &lt;em&gt;GetRegAthlete&lt;/em&gt; component, which is essentially just a registration form for the specified profile.&lt;/p&gt;
