&lt;h2 id=&quot;What-Are-Mongoose-Discriminators&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#What-Are-Mongoose-Discriminators&quot; aria-label=&quot;What Are Mongoose Discriminators permalink&quot; class=&quot;gatsby-remark-autolink before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;What Are Mongoose Discriminators?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&quot;The model dot discriminator function is part of Mongoose (a popular MongoDB library for Node.js). They are a schema inheritance mechanism. They enable you to have multiple models with overlapping schemas on top of the same underlying MongoDB collection.&quot; - &lt;strong&gt;mongoose docs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are three topics around Mongoose Discriminators, and we are going to cover them one by one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Default Mongoose Behahvior&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Discriminator Keys&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;My Take&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;Default-Mongoose-Behavior&quot; style=&quot;position:relative;&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Default-Mongoose-Behavior&quot; aria-label=&quot;Default Mongoose Behavior permalink&quot; class=&quot;gatsby-remark-autolink before&quot;&gt;&lt;svg aria-hidden=&quot;true&quot; focusable=&quot;false&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; version=&quot;1.1&quot; viewBox=&quot;0 0 16 16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot;&gt;&lt;path fill-rule=&quot;evenodd&quot; d=&quot;M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z&quot;&gt;&lt;/path&gt;&lt;/svg&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Default Mongoose Behavior&lt;/h2&gt;
